casebody.data:
Kene, Respondent, v. Bergholz, Appellant. (Supreme Court, General Term, Second Department. December 10, 1890.) Appeal from circuit court, Westchester county.

Argued before Dykman and Pratt, J J.

J. M. Ferguson, for appellant. Isaac N. Mills, for respondent. Pratt, J.

There is nothing involved in this case but a question of fact, which was fairly submitted to the jury, and is settled by their verdict. Judgment affirmed, with costs.
